parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake vacuum pump can cause the brake pedal to become hard to press, leading to extended stopping distances and increased risk of accidents.

the brake pedal sinks to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the vehicle may not stop at all
a squeaking or squalling noise is heard when the brake pedal is applied
